- 4 tbsp olive oil
- 1 Large white onion
- 2 medium carrots
- 3 celery stalks
- 1 tsp smoked sea salt
- 1/4 bottle red wine
- 1 tbsp soy sauce
- 1 tbsp chipotle chullula hot sauce
- 1 shot espresso
- 15g 70% chocolate
- 250g tomatoes
- 2 tsp smoked paprika
- 1 tsp ground cumin
- 1 tsp ground corriander
- 3 big cloves garlic
- 4 big red chillies
- 1/2 tsp fresh cracked back pepper
- 50g fresh corriander
- 1 veg stock cube
- 400g canned kidney beans in water

---

1. Pre heat large dutch oven on hob at mediun.
2. Fine dice onion, grate carrots and celery, for celery discard stringy remains after grating.
3. Add olive oil to pot, and tsp smoked sea salt
4. Add Onion, carrot, and celery to pot and cook out for 20 mins until most moisture removed and veg has light colour.
5. Add red wine and stock, reduce for 10 mins
6. Chop tomoatoes into quarters, add to pot, let cook for ten mins.
7. Dice garlic, chillies, and stalks of fresh corriander, add to pot with soy sauce, chullula, espresso, and chocolate.
8. Cook out for 10 mins
9. Add whole can of kidney beans, with the bean water, add paprika, cumin, and dried corriander,
10. Reduce on low for 1hr, or until yoghurt thick
11. Let cool, for 1hr, then add diced fresh corriander and black pepper.  Stir through and check for seasoning
